# Enrich — Capabilities

Apply when mapping skills to evidence, building competency matrix, or after enriching projects/experience/certs.

Usually run **after** other records exist so `evidence` links are populated.

## Target file

`ai-agents/database/capabilities.json` → `records[]`

## Record shape

```json
{
  "id": "cap-{skill-slug}",
  "name": "AWS / Terraform",
  "category": "cloud | backend | architecture | frontend | ai | devops | qa | leadership",
  "level": "strong | working | learning",
  "evidence": {
    "projectCacheIds": ["terraform-aws-infrastructure"],
    "experienceIds": [],
    "certificationIds": ["cert-aws-saa"],
    "reviewIds": [],
    "outcomeIds": []
  },
  "keywords": ["iac", "terraform", "aws"],
  "audience": ["employers", "clients"],
  "sourceIds": [],
  "confidence": "verified",
  "enrichment_status": "complete",
  "enriched_at": "...",
  "enriched_by": "cursor"
}
```

## Steps

1. `level: "strong"` only with 2+ evidence types OR one major project + cert.
2. Derive capabilities from new experience/CV — do not invent skills without evidence.
3. When `projects.cache.json` entry lists competencies, link `projectCacheId` instead of duplicating prose.

## Rules

- Prefer merging into existing `cap-{slug}` records.
- `learning` for certs-in-progress or course-only without delivery proof.
- This file powers `/capabilities` page logic later — keep ids stable.
